To multiply, first multiply numerators and denominators, then simplify:

\[
- \tfrac{1}{3}\times \tfrac{12}{7}
= \frac{-1\cdot12}{3\cdot7}
= \frac{-12}{21}
= -\frac{4}{7}.
\]

To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
\frac{2}{3}\;\div\;\frac{1}{6}
=\frac{2}{3}\times\frac{6}{1}
=\frac{2\cdot6}{3\cdot1}
=\frac{12}{3}
=4.
\]

To subtract, combine the numerators over the common denominator and then simplify:

\[
- \frac{31}{30} \;-\;\frac{7}{30}
=\;\frac{-31 - 7}{30}
=\;\frac{-38}{30}
=\;-\frac{19}{15}.
\]

To subtract, rewrite \(2/3\) with denominator \(12\):  
\(2/3 = 8/12\).  
Then  
\[
\frac{11}{12} - \frac{8}{12}
= \frac{11-8}{12}
= \frac{3}{12}
= \frac{1}{4}.
\]

To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
\frac{4}{11}\div\frac{2}{7d}
=\frac{4}{11}\times\frac{7d}{2}
=\frac{4\cdot7d}{11\cdot2}
=\frac{28d}{22}
=\frac{14d}{11}.
\]
